# Tabbify Workspace sshd drop-in. exec / IDE-remote land as the UNPRIVILEGED
# `agent` uid — NEVER root (spec §4: the agent must not read the GitHub token,
# the broker socket, or any cap-URL). The node's exec proxy + the laptop user's
# pubkey (appended by the broker, §12 S6) connect on the mesh ULA; the ULA + the
# injected key ARE the trust boundary.
#
# Installed as /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/tabbify-workspace.conf (overrides the base).
Port 2222
ListenAddress ::
ListenAddress 0.0.0.0
AllowUsers agent
PermitRootLogin no
PasswordAuthentication no
PubkeyAuthentication yes
AuthorizedKeysFile /home/agent/.ssh/authorized_keys
# StrictModes off: the §12-S6 add-key is mediated by the privileged `broker` uid,
# so ~agent/.ssh is group-writable (group `agent`, which `broker` is a member of)
# — the broker appends the laptop key there. Default StrictModes would reject a
# group-writable ~/.ssh. This does NOT weaken the trust boundary: the mesh ULA +
# the keys in authorized_keys ARE the boundary, and the key is appended ONLY via
# the token-gated :8732 broker endpoint (the agent has no token; it cannot add a
# key that lets anyone NEW in — only the node, holding the authkeys cap, can).
StrictModes no
# No DNS in the microVM; skip reverse-DNS auth checks.
UseDNS no
